reviews.review_text: I had received such a caring and Knowledgeable service from Della at this location. Even though it wasn t her expertise , she went out of the way to help me find all the items; those I was looking under a lot of stress to get a problem fixed at our house. Keep up the good work Della! You are very nice human being!

Another amazing experience at Home Depot Terminal (Vancouver). I had a very complicated return, 3 items, and 3 different scenarios, but Nifemi handled it perfectly! She investigated, got to the bottom of it, and was a rockstar through it all. A manager had to come in and help, and he was great as well. This is not my closest Home Depot, but I will go out of my way to come here. Every single staff member I deal with is awesome, with a huge care meter and so willing to help. You can tell this store is managed well!

Went to Home Depot to purchase a new fridge. Start to finish, it was quick and easy. They have a wide selection to choose from. The only down side was when we received our Fridge, there was 2 small dents; one on each side of the french doors. Sid Moosavi, that works in appliances was the one that helped us from the time of purchase. He was very helpful and resolved the issue immediately. I enjoyed the experience of purchasing with Home Depot. 10/10 would recommend and will definitely purchase at this location again.
Great place to train a pup. Ya they got good hardware and tools too   @homedepot contact me for licensing lol.

Great location, finally found what I needed. Went across the whole lower mainland to find this. Watch where youre driving, things can get dodgy pretty quick. What I thought was a camping ground of digital nomads was nowhere near that. My fault for being so presumptuous, egg on my face. From now on Ill never walk into another persons tent and ask how much Bitcoin do you own.

Lots of great prices and very cool gadgets! I will note that the lady in charge of the self-checkouts was extremely good at what she does. Amazing customer service, and that feels great since its lacking in so many places. Great experience here. Give that lady a raise!

Very large garden centre with a big selection of various plants and tropical plants. Most of the plants are the same ones you will find at high end garden stores but much cheaper at Home Depot.  Staff friendly and available to help when needed.

TOOL RENTAL REVIEW -- I was recommended to rent a nail gun to fix the fallen bottoms of my kitchen cabinets so i did but the nails proved to not be strong enough for my repair job. Took it back to home depot and also brought my cabinets in with me and explained the situation to Ken Nguey and Saksham. They quickly identified that I needed a much stronger staple gun to perform the repair so instead of charging me for one, they took one from the rental section and helped me repair my shelves on the spot as it required an air compressor which i didnt have access to either. My shelves are fully repaired now and I am extremely happy with the service I received. Keep up the good work guys!

The store is well organized and clean. Maybe not the biggest, but for sure you can find almost everything you need for your home and garden. Quick update: the best garden center! I found here plants that I couldnt find in nurseries and at an amazing good price.
Purchased a power tool today, the guy gave me good advices and was very knowledgeable. Absolutely great customer service 10/10.
This is the best home depot. I got some lumber from here and Nikhil.N helped me alot. I recommend everyone to ask for Nikhil.N if you are looking for something in Lumber section.
I received a great service as usual. They priced matched my purchase with the online price. The delivery was very convenient.

Most of the time I perches my materials from this Home Depot because parking is convenient and they Mach the price, today I bought drywall wall the cashier Jasjit was very helpful ans even call for associate to help me loading my truck that young man was very helpful and nice too, I forgot his name .

All in all, an excellent experience that will draw me back to Home Depot again. Needed to buy a washer and dryer. Chose Home Depot after much research (online) as having the right models at the best prices. Went to the store to finalise my choice and was entirely pleased with the visit. They had a good display of many appliances. I was helped by a great staff member called Gloria Miranda, who was knowledgeable, capable and efficient.  Apart from her professional expertise, she was also friendly and attentive and guided me through various decisions well while offering what discounts she could. I left having ordered the washer and dryer I wanted, most happily.

I just want to say that I experienced exceptional service at the Home Depot, Terminal Ave., Vancouver today. When I asked for directions, I was taken to the place where the plants were, and Olive, bless her heart, she actually loaded in my topsoil for me. Everyone was in a very customer service oriented mood, and it was a real pleasure to shop there. The choices of plants were abundant and they were all good quality. However, the prices have gone up quite substantially since last summer. It is still my  go to  place for home gardening materials.
For my work, my co-worker and I are constantly here getting all the items we need for our work projects. Great selection and staff are very helpful.
Very good customer service from staff, Raj in the tool department. He helped me quickly find a drill I was looking for and also placed an order for a sale item available only online.

Huge selection of home improvement and gardening supplies. The staff are helpful and friendly. Keep an eye out for their seasonal transition sales, and always check a few different products to make sure you get the best price (deWalt impact driver and screw kit was only $50 more expensive than just the impact driver, but you got 2 batteries in the kit, and a certificate for another pkg of two 20v batteries).

This store is very well organized. The staff is very friendly, flexible, and willing to help. Connor in the hardware department has been running around to help me find different things. He also showed me how to use the pipe cutter. The customer service manager is also very helpful! Thank you, Home Depot! Good job

Home Depot has been always my first choice, but this time, in the last working hour of Sunday, I totally experienced a very higher level of service, provided by these Gentlemen (Goe and Samar), moreover, their product knowledge was impressive as well.

Francisco was a great help. He knows his products and was able to help us with our queries within minutes while also teaching us how we can go about it in the future. If you are in hardware needs at Home Depot, Francisco is the guy for it.
I am always amazed just how friendly and helpful the employees are at all the branches. Very much above and beyond every time. Do they actively poach staff from other companies?

My experience today was beyond imagination of a person be so kind and helpful to the others and his name was SAURABH he was working in garden center and his help was beyond of a person could do as a staff, while  there were other staff take it easy and try to do to minimum. This is an opportunity for me to say thank you so much to him for being so honest for what he does as a staff works at home depot, myself and my husband are so thankful and all our good wishes and our blessing for him to stablish himself for greater future as a kind honest pure hard worker . Thank you Best regards

I bought a piece of wood board there as my computer desktop, but I forgot to bring a measuring tape. The Mexican uncle at the cash register kindly lent me one. Then, they also offered free on-site cutting service for customers. I had a small piece left over from the cutting, but the technician said it was okay to leave it there. I really like their customer service there.

The 1 minute key copy machine is a must! By far, the location at 900 Terminal Ave, Vancouver is great place to invest. I have experienced in each visit that the employers are so knowledgeable. I received a great advice today and I grab a Varathane Aged Wood Accelerator and a Watco Butcher Block oil & Conditioner for my new furniture design project, and as a cherry on top,  right outside is a beautiful street art.
First 2023 Christmas purchase..for the past several years, my Sister in Ontario and I have an ongoing dialogue about if we have enough lights....So....
Alison in garden section is such an amazing employee with an amazing heart helped me with my plants and selection.

While I do have a bias towards enjoying Home Depot I am also keenly aware and have experienced employees who do not really know their section. To some degree I understand this and accept it as part of a larger employer picture. My wifes and my experience buying a vanity set up, however, was made truly enjoyable by a woman who found us looking at faucets. Her apron bore the name Blessing and we came to know this was entirely appropriate. She helped us well past our initial query and seemed to take on the project as if it were hers to invest into down to the last detail. She was knowledgeable, fun to shop with, and well exceeded our expectations. We had a great time and felt totally secure in our decisions with the apt and encouraging advice. Thank you Blessing!
This store is one of their best. Recommend. Contractor or Home owner this place has what you likely need. Larger selection than most.
Can t complain staff was very helpful you just got to find them or ask for help!

This Home Depot has just about everything that you could ever look for! Today though I came to get garden hoses, nozzles, and I was hoping to get some plants. The hoses and the nozzles were a very good price point and seem to be good value and construction. Unfortunately I found their vegetables a little picked over and the prices a little steep still. But if I had been looking for flowers, oh my goodness did they ever have a fabulous selection and they look very healthy as well. Their staff was very helpful.
Francisco from hardware made my life sooooo easy! Kudos to that guy for helping and going extra mile. Gave me knowledge about how to pick tools and fasteners
Nice store big box furniture store like any other stores in the U.S A staff name Seeyoum from Ethiopia was very helpful and outstanding customer service

NAM LE , he really helpful , he helped me alot around to pickup some things around garden,  heavy soils bag , , bringing them to pay , to my car... Such a very nice helpful, friendly, nicee guy. Thanks a lot   Nam Le.

I love Home Depot!! Definitely surpasses its competitors in price, product quality, and customer service. I had a great experience last week at Home Depot (HD) @ Terminal Ave with an associate (Lucy L.) She s exceptional at customer service with expert kitchen design skills. A big thank you to Lucy for going above and beyond to help solve some of my kitchen problems. She answered all my questions and was very creative in solving my renovation design issues. There s a Home Depot that s closer to my house. I drive the extra 5km because the service (Lucy/Emily) and product range far surpasses all other HD locations in the lower mainland. Customers appreciate honest and expert advice. I hope head office acknowledges employees. Show your customers corporate is listening and values our feedback.  I d like to shop at a store that values its staff. So Please do that. People matter
Today, I must have spoken to 10+ staff Every single one was friendly & super helpful! Bring back Harveys!

I went in to Home Depot on Terminal the other day to rent a drill. I own a drill but couldnt for the life of me find it anywhere and needed to get the task done. All I needed to do was drill a few holes of various sizes into a wooden box (to hide charging cables for my devices). My plan was to rent the drill, do the job there and then and then turn it back in. The guy who helped me was Ken. He was a super nice guy. Not only did he not charge me for the drill, he drilled all the holes for me while I held the box in place! You just dont get that kind of service or total customer service attitude much anymore and I really appreciated it. It meant a lot to me. I go to that store a lot and this just made me feel even better about the place. Thank you very much for your help, Ken! Youre a good guy and Home Depot is lucky to have you! Derek

Man was I ever in a pickle I got a free countertop dishwasher and the attachment wasnt clicking on to my faucet properly. So it turned in to quite a head-scratcher after several hours online and a visit to a plumbing specialty store who also went to great lengths to helpe out, sent me to home Depot where the associates went above and beyond their duty to help me figure out how to attach this to my sink so I am very grateful to them. Im quite handy and know how to fix a lot of things and am often spoken down to buy male associates especially but these two associates worked very hard to troubleshoot this with me and I am sorry to all the other customers because I did dominate their time but they solved a huge problem for me and Im forever thankful.

As soon as l stepped into the store, a lovely lady welcomed me and showed me where I could find what I wanted. However, the store was busy lots of staff were around and helped people. The name of the gentleman who helped me was Aashish. He was so knowledgeable in a minute; He showed me what I needed. Then gave me more information around. It was so beautiful experienced. I highly recommend this location which also is convenient for parking as well.

Able to rent a van fairly quickly. Booked online 2 days prior and received an email about 10 hours prior confirming my reservation. I got the van within 10 minutes of my arrival. And returning it was equally quick.
Today I came here for buying some shelves and wood sheets. What a great service by  Gurman . What a professional guy. Thanks alot hone depot team
Got all I needed for my small project!

Was a little short staff but also the person being served had many questions. The person serving them was patient. Ivy (at Terminal window covering) was very helpful and friendly. Not only she gave her honest advice she took the time after cutting my blinds to show me a demo on how to install. Very happy with service today at Home Depot Terminal Ave location.

I just had the best experience at this Home Depot. Im a beginner trying to make some decorations for an event and all of the staff here went above and beyond to make sure I got what I needed. Everyone was so helpful, especially Basant, who answered many of my beginner questions and took a lot of his time to help me cut wood into the pieces I needed for my projects. He really cared and wanted me to succeed. I really appreciate all of the great service I received and friendliness I experienced!
Gardening Season has started Good selection of indoor / outdoor plants.

Bill from Tool Rentals, such an amazing human being! We had to book a van for moving and gave him our number, he called us back as soon as a van was available. We forgot to get out insurance papers, he patiently waited for us to return. It was near closing time and there was a long line of customers, however, Bill did not lose patience and assisted everyone! He is the best at what he does and his patience, customer service & attitude is commendable! This was the best customer service experience Ive had in my entire life! Cheers to Bill!
WOW. Today, I was blown away by the help I received from Ed. His knowledge and professionalism- unbelievable! Ed truly deserves recognition.

To the southeast of the store where Glen drive ends there is a dirt road. At high noon most days if you clear your mind and let go of all earthly worries a spirit will appear. Follow the spirit to the garden centre where you will enter through a secret side door. You will be invisible to all the humans present. Take 1 of whatever you want but ONLY 1. And make sure you go back exactly the way you came to exit this parallel dimension or you will reside here forever separate. The spirit will bid you farewell when your journey is complete.

Yesterday, I went to the Home Depot terminal branch with a large list of items to purchase for my company. I was confused looking for items. The floor staff were helpful, but I came across a gentleman whose name was Kevin, if I remember correctly. He was exceptionally helpful and knowledgeable in every department; he made my shopping trip less stressful and found all the items that I required. Even an item that was thought not to be on the shelf, Kevin took the extra mile, brought out a large ladder and found it for me in no time. I really appreciate your help Mr. Kevin! God bless you. Many Thanks, Karim

I have been at your store four times in the last two weeks, and i was very satisfied of the help I got from Sarah at the blinds department previous employees they told me they didn t have any because the compute was showing none .Sarah was so nice with a great idea ti grab the ladder and check the upper shelves where she found four. Well done Sarah much appreciated. Also another good and pleasant and knowledgeable employee is Ed Millworker where I purchased insulation, three bundles of base board and other things. Thank you Ed well done .
Thank you for your help Amit.  Great customer service

The most home depot of all home depots: Friendly, professional and knowledge staff. Last time I was looking for drapes with specific sizes and requirements. The woman (Im so sorry I forgot your name..) in the blinds/drapes department helped me out and went above and beyond. I mentioned this was my first time replacing window curtain fixtures and she was very accommodating and helpful based on my novice experience. She provided a lot of advice and suggestions from the type of fixture down to the color of the drapes. Overall with her help, my decision on this purchase was fast and efficient.

I was picking up an order of  blinds that were very long in their  shipping packaging at this location. A Sales Representative  at the Customer Service desk, Burton went out of his way to help me to bring them and fit into my car! He was extremely nice with excellent customer service skills! Thanks again Burton, HD can be proud of employees like you!

We had an amazing experience thanks to a kind employee who assisted us, Umish. He had great customer service, helped with informing us about the different qualities and options for vanities. I really appreciated his honesty and helpfulness. Overall a great experience!
Huge store, but its not easy to get there . Far from station
Extremely helpful staff ans great selection. Umesh personally helped us find everything we were looking for and even kept my 4 year old engaged while we worked through my list. Amazing service.

Thank you to Tim and Sid for giving very useful advices for home appliances. Without your help, this process would be so much harder. They both worked above and beyond our expectation - they not only answered all our questions but also suggested things which we would need in the future installation process. They helped us save time, money as well as prevented stress for us in the future. They were both very kind, understanding and efficient.

We had a kitchen Designed by Izabella at Home Depot on Terminal Ave.  Oh wow!  Shes a thousand times more skilled than her colleagues in other Branches.  Shes attentive. Friendly and the Princess of Customer service. Big thanks

Bought a washer dryer from Home Depot today and the staff was amazing. The lady helping my was named Gloria and she was extremely informative, helped me out with what washer/dryer would work with my space as well as what the differences between all the models are. All round awesome experience, machines are arriving next week to be installed!

Great experience with Calvin. He went above and beyond in his service . I was looking for grout cleaner in isle 4.  He was walking by towards the cashier area and when I asked him he walked me all the way to the grout isle in the back of the store. (He could ve just said isle whatever) I then asked him about grout scrubbers and he walked me back to isle 3 and picked it out for me.  That s service above and beyond .

I m a Home Depot fan. They have everything you need, knowledgeable, friendly staff and a reasonable return policy. I ve had them go above and beyond in service. Sometimes they get crazy busy and may seem a little understaffed, stay kind folks.
You know these guys rent vehicles? Its a really good deal too. Rented a small flatbed truck for a day. Very happy with how it worked out.

I am so excited to share my experince today. I met two real human being in Homedepot Terminal Ave, Vancouver. I met MANO and BRIAN in store#7042, TOOL RENTAL department. They changed my mood and treat me in the best way possible. They were so kind and supportive that I could not find the proper word to show how grateful I am. I remember these gentlemen for the rest of my life. I appreciate you, guys.

Great location, easy in and out Home Depot associates are hit and miss (like all businesses these days). If you want experience, patience,  and kindness (very hard to find these days) Ask for BEN (5+ stars) Hands Down hes the best HD Associate I have ever dealt with.
Got the part I needed, good inventory, price is constant and competitive.
Good prices and kind staff.

Lucy was amazing at helping me buy a laundry machine, she approached me which was great she was very quick, we finished the pruchase in less than 10min. This is by far the best HOME DEPOT i have visited and i will only come here and do business with Lucy. Thank you

The staff on this day was informative and efficient. What I liked most was that they wayed in my options for the drain snake I rented. It seems simple enough to an average person and even more simple to a trades person like myself but they got to the point with questions and alternatives.
Key machine works fast and great. Cool stuff lol
Best Home Depot in Vancouver. Most friendly and knowledgeable staff ive seen so far compare to both home depot and canadian tire. My first choice to buy anything

Home depot, regardless of the location, is and always has been excellent. I was greeted upon entering the store and directed to the proper section where I meet a staff who was able to answer my questions. Better yet, the staff gave me a few small parts (screws) for free and explain the alternative to my problem. I ended up following this advice and bought a new faucet where I was also welcomed and advised properly on the right product to purchase and the assurance that it would fit the existing place. Thank you home depot for training your staff the right way and to give them the proper knowledge to advise your clients.

Easy to get to building and hardware mega store. Went in to buy a bunch of casters, which they had. (Whenever Ive needed something from rat poison to specific screws, theyve always had it.) Easy to get to, easy to get out to Terminal. Thats my highlights.

Great location, lots of parking, well stocked, and easy to locate products via the web app. Like always, shop around other non big-box stores for better pricing on building materials. HD Ive found to be on the mid-range for lumber price if buying bulk. After todays visit, I was quite surprised by the abundance of staff available for assistance!

I m a lady that not own any tools. I watched couple of YouTube videos and went to Home Depot. I don t remember who was but I felt so Lucky with that staff whom were so knowledgeable in tile department that day. I grabbed stuff that he recommended and I Literally, finished washroom by myself. Thank you!
Great service and affordable pricing. Purchase lumber to complete my deck. Good quality wood.

A special shout out to John, one of the managers, on shift tonight, Saturday, March 27, 2021.  Went to this Home Depot location after the glazed pots I wanted was no longer available at another location nearby.  Got to the store only to find out that the pot was $4.98 rather than the $2.00 in the first store I went to.  Told John about it and without hesitation he matched the lower price.  Really appreciate him and the rest of the staff for being so helpful.
I love the big Home Depot for the occasional visit.
Why is it so hard to get help at any home depot  Well but when I do find someone the person is usually quite helpful.
Huge parking lot of free of charge What, more could you ask for
good experience although their plumbing supplies are lacking hangers and supports. only fittings and some valves. overall I still love the home depot

While we shop quite a bit at Home Depot,  its ALWAYS hard to find someone in customer service. We moved here about 2 years ago and were held hostage by Home Depot because we ordered special hardwood flooring and were told to wait until there was installers available. We waited for close to 1 month, and our flooring was just sitting there waiting for installation. We couldnt do anything until we had the flooring installed   so finally,  we picked it up ourselves and had someone,  who did a fabulous job, install it for us beginning the day after we contacted him. Finally,  we decorated our new home and didnt have to be camping in our home any longer. Two weeks later,  we got a call from Home Depot advising that they still didnt have an installer available but should have one in about 2 weeks. The person who called actually got upset when we told them that we had it installed by someone who was available.!!! I can honestly say that I have never seen such bad service from any operation, especially considering that we bought top of the line flooring and have spent a lot of money at Home Depot both in Vancouver and now here. We continue to shop there, but know enough not to try to find any service & find what we need on our own. That being said,  Home Depot have an excellent selection and their prices are very reasonable. Just dont expect much in the customer service area.

The plumbing associate, older Asian gentleman, is always on point. He is knowledagble, is happy to help, always answers your questions without rushing and knows where everything in his department is. He has made my shopping experience very smooth in the last few times that I was there.

They were very helpful, I was given detailed instructions of exactly how to find what I needed and once there, while trying to decide what to buy of my choices, another staff member came up and explained each and gave me even more info on how to get the best results from the electronic device. If not for him, I would have brought them home and set them up wrong, resulting in failure to work and thus a return on the product. I appreciated the extra help immensely as we really need the product working now not later and also being in a wheelchair to have to make a waste of extra trips only to find out it was my misuse, for a question I didnt know to ask, I am very grateful. It being my first time in the store, it was also nice to be in store that is definitely wheelchair friendly. Considering how fast the staff member came to ask if I needed help, I know that had I not had someone with me, I wouldnt have had to wait or go searching for anyone to help me reach anything either. Love the really wide aisles!! If the store had been busy I probably still wouldnt have felt like I was in the way of people or worrying about taking knuckles out to get passed others  .

Been here a few times now & have been consistently impressed by the detailed knowledge of every staff member I approached with questions about certain products. They all know so much, not just about their specific department, but about the store overall, and they were super helpful in getting me what I needed and explaining how things work. This may be a  big box  store, but I really appreciated the personal, professional  service.

Perfectly happy with a customer service with Mr Nikhil due to disability condition this gentleman. was very helpful, arranged to the cash counter, arranged assistance to lift up my goods into my vehicle. Thank you very much  Mr Nikhil you really need a big tap, Ive never got service. Im a frequent customer to Home Depot but Ive never got the Service as what you did for me very.what you did for me by Home Depot Vancouver

Was there: 5 Oct 2016 around 6-7pm I love their customer service. I came in and started grabbing things and realized I needed a cart. I ask a lady and she happily went and got one for me. I was looking for items and instead of the person giving up, they get me to the person who knows where to find the item Im looking for. Everyone is very helpful. The prices are okay, not cheap or not expensive. They have everything you can imagine. Love their customer support!

I had great experience visiting store on Terminal Ave! Kieran helped me with door hinges. Hes very helpful and resourceful young man, who didnt mind to take extra step to help me with my problem! THANK you, Kieran, a lot!!

Definitely my favourite Home Depot location. It is always accurately stocked (online stock efficient as well). Theyre always busy but try hard to work towards customer service. They always help load my bigger items in my car. I only go to this location for my Home Depot needs.
Very helpful staff in the tile department. We found a couple beautiful tiles for our bathroom renovation with their help and at a great price.

The associates I requested help from were patient with answering my questions. They gave good advice after asking whether I want to apply the product outdoors or indoors, and what products would work best.

One of the best tool-buying experiences ever (and I buy a lot of tools).  The salesperson proactively asked if needed help and I mentioned that I saw a particular tool at a local tool store for a lower price.  We verified the price and he made sure that he beat the competitors price by 10% as he walked me to the cashier to approve it. He handed me his business card (as the department manager) and said to come see the store if I found a lower price at any of the other local tool shops.

So my key got stuck in one of those 1 minute machine, Sabine to the rescue with pliers and pulled it out. Than cut our key manually and helped us out. Awesome job!!! Turned my negative experience into a positive one.

Other than the materials, appliances and supplies for home renovation and daily living needs, they also provide specialists in home design of closets, kitchen counters, etc. The prices are very reasonable and service quality are excellent. For kitchen cabinets, they provide custome reface, costing a lot less money and time to improve the appearance of the kitchen. Their installation of dish washer is about $159. Some other service charged me $600 for the job. My lessons learned: check with Home Depot first when doing renovation.

A very easily accessible location. Plenty of parking. Well stocked, helpful staff.  As always, if you know the layout of most HD stores its easy to find what you want.  Big large signs shows you where things are. Self checkout and cashiers are available.  Many forms of payments accepted with email receipts

Great management service, lots store department heads or sales are helpful.  This is the largest Home Depot branch in Vancouver, they have the most inventory and selection.  The hardwood floor department lost one of my bought merchandises in the storage, the manager on duty immediately dealt with exceeding my full satisfaction.  Love this store!!! Will come back.

Huge thank you to your employee Van at the customer service at this Terminal location for all the help during my curbside pickup mishap this week. 10/10 customer service and quick resolution for a situation that could have been quite an inconvenience for us otherwise - give that girl a raise! Thanks, Van!

I needed to paint my place. I had never gone to a store to buy all the neccessary tools to paint. An older gentleman if Indian decent named Jay was in the paint section. He made my shopping experience so smooth, I was not nervous at all. This is not my first time in a Home Depot, but this man made this trip very memorable! Thank you Jay!!
tiles wood paint hose clamps and washers and dryers. I remember when I had to go to twelve different stores to buy this 3 things

We were from out of town (Northern Alberta out of town) went to find the items we were searching for were available in their store.  They were 82  curtain rods and we needed 6..... but we were flying home    !  Anyway Ben (on Sunday March 14) saved the day!  He was so helpful & did what he could for us.   He wrapped them up for us so we could take them on our flight!  Thanks Ben
GREG at PRO desk had my whole deck order ready, right down to every screw!! He changed my mind to safer products and saved me lots of money on others. Way worth the trip from Pender Harbour
